1
00:00:21,897 --> 00:00:23,524
I need…

2
00:00:27,653 --> 00:00:29,655
I need somewhere…

3
00:00:33,409 --> 00:00:34,952
A secluded spot…

4
00:00:51,093 --> 00:00:52,470
Somewhere out of sight…

5
00:01:31,425 --> 00:01:33,552
Well, I'll get going then.

6
00:01:38,015 --> 00:01:40,810
What is it?
Is something the matter, Simon?

7
00:01:40,893 --> 00:01:43,979
Chloe, someone's there.

8
00:01:47,566 --> 00:01:51,695
I don't want any trouble.
I'll leave right away.

9
00:01:55,825 --> 00:01:57,618
I'm terribly sorry.

10
00:02:03,791 --> 00:02:05,459
So…

11
00:02:06,168 --> 00:02:08,087
Should I report her or something?

12
00:02:08,838 --> 00:02:10,130
I suppose.

13
00:02:17,221 --> 00:02:18,305
What now?

14
00:02:19,598 --> 00:02:21,809
I'm scared… She's creeping me out.

15
00:02:34,613 --> 00:02:36,073
-Chloe.
-Emma.

16
00:02:36,156 --> 00:02:37,366
-Chloe et Emma.
-Chloe et Emma.

17
00:02:43,747 --> 00:02:48,836
TEN DAYS LATER

18
00:02:59,889 --> 00:03:02,266
Welcome to Shingetsu Nathan's
Hall of Divination.

19
00:03:02,349 --> 00:03:04,518
HALL OF DIVINATION
READ YOUR FORTUNE

20
00:03:05,978 --> 00:03:07,563
Soar, dragon!

21
00:03:07,646 --> 00:03:09,440
SOAR, DRAGON!

22
00:03:12,026 --> 00:03:13,360
CONSULTING THE STARS…

23
00:03:18,115 --> 00:03:21,660
TODAY'S FORTUNE - THINGS WILL
GO DOWNHILL BE PROACTIVE

24
00:03:26,457 --> 00:03:27,875
I'm sorry.

25
00:03:27,958 --> 00:03:31,170
I'm the one who owes you an apology.
I was zoned out.

26
00:03:31,253 --> 00:03:35,132
PUBLIC EMPLOYMENT SERVICE CENTER

27
00:03:37,885 --> 00:03:38,886
Say…

28
00:03:41,722 --> 00:03:45,142
Isn't this fried piroshki
the new item from the convenience store?

29
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:46,810
I've been wanting to try one.

30
00:03:47,978 --> 00:03:49,563
Is it new?

31
00:03:49,647 --> 00:03:52,066
It costs less than 200 yen, right?

32
00:03:52,149 --> 00:03:54,902
Wait, 150 yen? Really, and it's this big?

33
00:03:54,985 --> 00:03:57,237
Yes, that's about how much it cost.

34
00:03:57,321 --> 00:04:01,033
And it's piroshki,
so it's stuffed with juicy, meaty filling.

35
00:04:01,116 --> 00:04:04,536
It's fried, meaning it's high in calories
and will power you through the entire day.

36
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:07,623
It's just the food
for someone seeking employment.

37
00:04:07,706 --> 00:04:09,416
I'll buy the same thing for lunch.

38
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:14,380
Say…

39
00:04:15,506 --> 00:04:17,967
Would you like to join me for lunch?

40
00:04:19,218 --> 00:04:22,054
I was just thinking
about eating at a park nearby.

41
00:04:23,472 --> 00:04:25,557
A park? I'm sold.

42
00:04:32,898 --> 00:04:34,066
Delicious.

43
00:04:39,613 --> 00:04:43,283
To tell you the truth, I bought it
because I thought it was curry bread.

44
00:04:43,367 --> 00:04:46,996
What? That's not remotely the same thing.
Are you okay?

45
00:04:47,079 --> 00:04:49,123
Right, it's an entirely different food.

46
00:04:50,624 --> 00:04:51,834
Recently…

47
00:04:53,585 --> 00:04:56,755
I started to let go of the small things.
I simply don't care anymore.

48
00:04:58,716 --> 00:05:02,761
I can relate.
That's how I felt when I lost my job.

49
00:05:03,679 --> 00:05:04,972
Is it a common thing to feel?

50
00:05:15,357 --> 00:05:17,192
I'm Emma.

51
00:05:18,861 --> 00:05:21,905
And I'm Konagaya.

52
00:05:28,787 --> 00:05:31,874
Brown. That's my lucky color.

53
00:05:31,957 --> 00:05:34,918
Lucky color? What's that, fortune-telling?

54
00:05:35,002 --> 00:05:38,630
Yes. I recently met a fortune teller,
and she read my fortune.

55
00:05:38,714 --> 00:05:41,133
I've been into fortune-telling lately too.

56
00:05:44,011 --> 00:05:46,722
That might be another thing
we unemployed folks have in common.

57
00:05:47,765 --> 00:05:50,100
Like Shingetsu Nathan.

58
00:05:50,184 --> 00:05:52,519
That's who I was watching
when we bumped shoulders.

59
00:05:53,729 --> 00:05:55,689
He used to be all over TV.

60
00:05:55,773 --> 00:05:58,901
His catchphrase "Soar, dragon!"
was really popular at school.

61
00:06:00,944 --> 00:06:03,697
I came across a fortune teller
by pure luck.

62
00:06:03,781 --> 00:06:07,576
And I didn't plan for her
to read my fortune or anything.

63
00:06:07,659 --> 00:06:11,038
Honestly, I didn't expect
her predictions to come true.

64
00:06:11,121 --> 00:06:13,290
But they did. I was surprised.

65
00:06:13,373 --> 00:06:16,418
Really now.
What sort of predictions were they?

66
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:20,881
Well… Can I get into it?

67
00:06:22,341 --> 00:06:23,425
Sure.

68
00:06:25,886 --> 00:06:29,890
That night, I was looking
for somewhere to sleep on the streets.

69
00:06:31,809 --> 00:06:35,771
I found someone's porch
that seemed secluded,

70
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:38,899
and I laid down,
thinking I found a perfect spot.

71
00:06:38,982 --> 00:06:41,360
I had reached my limit. I was dead tired.

72
00:06:41,443 --> 00:06:45,030
That's when the resident found me.
Needless to say, she was shocked.

73
00:06:45,823 --> 00:06:48,075
I don't want any trouble.

74
00:06:48,158 --> 00:06:49,785
I'll leave right away.

75
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:55,749
I'm terribly sorry.

76
00:06:59,378 --> 00:07:02,756
In a panic, I apologized and took off,

77
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:05,050
but then, my stomach
started to hurt out of the blue.

78
00:07:10,472 --> 00:07:11,557
What now?

79
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:15,102
I'm scared… She's creeping me out.

80
00:07:19,106 --> 00:07:22,776
I'm sorry to impose, but…

81
00:07:23,569 --> 00:07:27,030
could I please use your restroom?

82
00:07:27,114 --> 00:07:28,949
It would be such a big help.

83
00:07:29,533 --> 00:07:30,784
-What?
-What?

84
00:07:36,915 --> 00:07:39,626
Thank you very much. You saved me.

85
00:07:40,627 --> 00:07:43,714
You'll freeze sleeping outside like that.

86
00:07:43,797 --> 00:07:44,798
Right.

87
00:07:44,882 --> 00:07:47,467
I poured some warm tea.
Would you like a cup?

88
00:07:48,802 --> 00:07:50,053
Could I?

89
00:07:50,721 --> 00:07:52,222
Thank you so much.

90
00:08:02,274 --> 00:08:04,610
Please enjoy these cookies too.

91
00:08:05,777 --> 00:08:06,945
You made my day.

92
00:08:07,571 --> 00:08:08,822
Thank you.

93
00:08:19,374 --> 00:08:20,667
Scrumptious.

94
00:08:21,835 --> 00:08:23,128
I baked them myself.

95
00:08:24,046 --> 00:08:26,215
Those are the leftovers.
Sorry there aren't many.

96
00:08:26,798 --> 00:08:29,384
I used whole wheat flour.
It's crunchy, isn't it?

97
00:08:29,468 --> 00:08:32,888
Yes, it's sure to keep me full. I love it.

98
00:08:32,971 --> 00:08:34,598
That's what makes you happy?

99
00:08:35,265 --> 00:08:36,308
It's tasty too.

100
00:08:38,727 --> 00:08:42,898
To start, why is a young woman like you
trying to sleeping outside?

101
00:08:45,108 --> 00:08:48,987
To tell you the truth,
I've been staying at Internet cafés.

102
00:08:49,071 --> 00:08:52,074
But I'm running out of money
and the prices go up on weekends.

103
00:08:52,157 --> 00:08:55,160
I was desperately trying to pinch pennies.

104
00:08:55,244 --> 00:08:56,453
Wait, what?

105
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:58,664
Are you a runaway?
Or do you not have a home?

106
00:08:58,747 --> 00:09:02,292
No. I was living with my ex,
but he's getting married.

107
00:09:02,376 --> 00:09:03,418
His fiancée is expecting.

108
00:09:03,502 --> 00:09:04,753
Sheesh.

109
00:09:05,629 --> 00:09:08,340
I used to live with my mother,

110
00:09:08,423 --> 00:09:11,843
but when I was 27,
she got sick and passed away.

111
00:09:12,886 --> 00:09:15,931
My ex-boyfriend, whom I was working with,

112
00:09:16,014 --> 00:09:17,933
asked if I wanted to move in with him.

113
00:09:18,016 --> 00:09:20,519
Wait, do you guys still work together?

114
00:09:21,228 --> 00:09:22,980
Well, the company went bankrupt.

115
00:09:25,899 --> 00:09:31,405
Apparently, the girl he got pregnant
lined up another job for him.

116
00:09:34,032 --> 00:09:38,912
Not only that, her parents are helping
with the down payment on a house.

117
00:09:41,081 --> 00:09:43,875
That's the realistic option, I guess.

118
00:09:46,795 --> 00:09:49,131
I went to the unemployment center,

119
00:09:49,214 --> 00:09:51,967
but I can't register an address
since I don't have a permanent place.

120
00:09:52,509 --> 00:09:55,387
So my job hunt hit a wall.

121
00:10:00,225 --> 00:10:01,560
You're cooked.

122
00:10:02,811 --> 00:10:04,396
Indeed I am.

123
00:10:06,189 --> 00:10:07,941
If you lived with your ex for a long time,

124
00:10:08,567 --> 00:10:11,570
can't you sue him and the woman
for compensation?

125
00:10:12,237 --> 00:10:14,364
I don't want to take it that far…

126
00:10:14,448 --> 00:10:17,200
He helped me
in my time of need, after all.

127
00:10:17,284 --> 00:10:22,581
Did your ex pay all the rent
and living expenses?

128
00:10:22,664 --> 00:10:24,958
No, we split them evenly.

129
00:10:25,042 --> 00:10:27,044
Then you guys were on equal ground.

130
00:10:27,127 --> 00:10:28,712
Not in the slightest.

131
00:10:28,795 --> 00:10:31,298
If I made him mad,
he could have kicked me out.

132
00:10:32,799 --> 00:10:35,260
You were walking on eggshells around him,

133
00:10:35,344 --> 00:10:38,096
but in the end, you still got kicked out.

134
00:10:44,353 --> 00:10:46,480
What am I supposed to do now?

135
00:10:51,568 --> 00:10:54,279
All I do is look up fortune reading
on the internet.

136
00:10:55,113 --> 00:10:57,407
It's the only thing
that gives me hope at this stage.

137
00:11:11,505 --> 00:11:14,257
Chloe, why don't you read her fortune?

138
00:11:15,133 --> 00:11:16,259
What?

139
00:11:18,595 --> 00:11:20,305
Are you a fortune teller?

140
00:11:21,932 --> 00:11:24,101
It's nothing that impressive.

141
00:11:24,184 --> 00:11:26,269
It's just a hobby of mine.

142
00:11:26,353 --> 00:11:28,522
It's more than a mere hobby.

143
00:11:29,940 --> 00:11:31,650
Then please.

144
00:11:33,026 --> 00:11:34,653
I don't care if it's inaccurate.

145
00:11:35,529 --> 00:11:36,947
I just need hope.

146
00:11:43,453 --> 00:11:46,873
Fortune-telling can accurately predict
your past and present.

147
00:11:47,416 --> 00:11:49,167
These things are set in stone.

148
00:11:50,085 --> 00:11:52,921
But reading the future
is a different story.

149
00:11:53,422 --> 00:11:56,174
Why, you ask? Why do you think that is?

150
00:11:59,136 --> 00:12:00,470
Well…

151
00:12:01,304 --> 00:12:04,558
Your actions determine your future.

152
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:06,852
The future isn't set in stone.

153
00:12:10,981 --> 00:12:14,109
If that's okay with you,
then I'll read your fortune.

154
00:12:22,242 --> 00:12:24,369
What is this room?

155
00:12:25,036 --> 00:12:28,582
My mediation room.
Isn't it relaxing in here?

156
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:41,344
Here.

157
00:12:41,428 --> 00:12:44,431
Please write down your name and birthday.

158
00:12:44,514 --> 00:12:45,599
Yes.

159
00:12:51,396 --> 00:12:52,689
SHO EMMA
JUNE 15TH, 1995

160
00:12:52,772 --> 00:12:55,192
Emma… Yoi?

161
00:12:55,984 --> 00:12:57,277
It's Sho Emma.

162
00:12:59,321 --> 00:13:00,405
"Sho Emma?"

163
00:13:01,072 --> 00:13:02,908
Don't call me that.
It sounds like "shame."

164
00:13:02,991 --> 00:13:04,701
You're 30 years old.

165
00:13:06,661 --> 00:13:08,246
We're around the same age.

166
00:13:32,270 --> 00:13:34,022
Mind taking a few steps back?

167
00:13:45,242 --> 00:13:46,243
Oh,

168
00:13:46,868 --> 00:13:48,078
mon…

169
00:13:50,247 --> 00:13:51,122
Dieu!

170
00:14:02,592 --> 00:14:06,429
She said I'd get caught up
in some incident in the near future.

171
00:14:06,513 --> 00:14:07,639
An incident?

172
00:14:09,933 --> 00:14:12,894
An incident with a fire.
Apparently, something to do with fire.

173
00:14:13,478 --> 00:14:16,731
But she said this incident would steer me
in the right direction.

174
00:14:16,815 --> 00:14:18,692
It doesn't make any sense, does it?

175
00:14:18,775 --> 00:14:19,818
Not really.

176
00:14:19,901 --> 00:14:22,404
I then had to pay her
the consultation fee, 1,000 yen.

177
00:14:22,487 --> 00:14:23,780
What?

178
00:14:23,863 --> 00:14:26,992
That was a big 1,000 yen for me.

179
00:14:27,075 --> 00:14:29,828
But she allowed me to spend a night.

180
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:34,207
Only for tonight, you hear me?

181
00:14:36,001 --> 00:14:37,127
Could I really?

182
00:14:38,086 --> 00:14:41,006
This guest house
is equipped with a shower.

183
00:14:41,089 --> 00:14:44,009
Please wash up before you get in the bed.

184
00:14:44,092 --> 00:14:45,260
Yes.

185
00:14:45,343 --> 00:14:47,721
I'm going back to the main house.

186
00:14:47,804 --> 00:14:50,974
Are you set up? Any other questions?

187
00:14:51,057 --> 00:14:53,393
No. Thank you so much.

188
00:14:54,311 --> 00:14:55,520
I'm happy for you.

189
00:14:55,604 --> 00:14:57,314
Yes, you guys saved me.

190
00:14:57,397 --> 00:14:59,524
Remember,
you're only staying one night, Sho Emma.

191
00:14:59,608 --> 00:15:00,609
I understand.

192
00:15:00,692 --> 00:15:01,693
Sho Emma?

193
00:15:03,028 --> 00:15:05,030
"Emma" is my surname,
and "Sho" is my name.

194
00:15:05,113 --> 00:15:07,490
Thank you,
for everything from the cookies to tea,

195
00:15:07,574 --> 00:15:11,036
then the restroom
and a night under your roof.

196
00:15:11,620 --> 00:15:13,204
We live in a dangerous world.

197
00:15:13,747 --> 00:15:17,083
Remember when an unhoused woman
was murdered at a bus stop?

198
00:15:17,626 --> 00:15:22,505
And recently,
a woman was murdered in Okutama.

199
00:15:22,589 --> 00:15:25,800
The last I heard,
the killer is still on the run.

200
00:15:27,218 --> 00:15:30,555
Simon, thank you for cleaning up.
Sorry to keep you till late.

201
00:15:31,222 --> 00:15:33,475
It's fine. Well, I must get going.

202
00:15:33,558 --> 00:15:37,604
I'll come again next week.
Good night, Chloe, Emma.

203
00:15:37,687 --> 00:15:39,022
Have a wonderful night.

204
00:15:47,238 --> 00:15:49,991
Is Simon originally from overseas?

205
00:15:53,578 --> 00:15:57,123
No. "Simon" is his surname.
His full name is Kenshiro Simon.

206
00:15:57,207 --> 00:15:58,708
Surname, huh.

207
00:15:58,792 --> 00:16:01,878
Also, I'm Kana Chloe.

208
00:16:01,961 --> 00:16:04,214
Kana meaning "god's name."

209
00:16:04,297 --> 00:16:07,133
I'm the owner of this house. I'm 32.

210
00:16:07,217 --> 00:16:08,677
I'm two years older than you, Sho Emma.

211
00:16:09,886 --> 00:16:12,514
It makes me a little uncomfortable
when you call me by my full name.

212
00:16:13,098 --> 00:16:14,307
Really now.

213
00:16:15,141 --> 00:16:16,393
Then…

214
00:16:18,436 --> 00:16:19,729
Miss Emma.

215
00:16:20,522 --> 00:16:21,648
Miss Emma?

216
00:16:25,860 --> 00:16:29,406
I don't keep any valuables in here,

217
00:16:29,489 --> 00:16:32,909
but please don't take necessities
like toilet paper with you.

218
00:16:32,992 --> 00:16:34,661
I've got your full name and your birthday,

219
00:16:34,744 --> 00:16:36,705
and I can call
the unemployment center for more info.

220
00:16:36,788 --> 00:16:39,958
You've been a huge help.
I wouldn't steal from you.

221
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:42,627
The bed and the restroom are upstairs.

222
00:16:43,420 --> 00:16:44,629
Good night.

223
00:16:53,930 --> 00:16:55,390
She…

224
00:16:56,182 --> 00:16:57,600
rubs me the wrong way, a little.

225
00:17:28,548 --> 00:17:30,550
What do I even do starting tomorrow?

226
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:39,350
Hello, Miss Emma!

227
00:17:40,477 --> 00:17:41,603
You awake?

228
00:17:42,687 --> 00:17:43,730
I'm up.

229
00:17:55,033 --> 00:17:57,827
Is something wrong?
Did you leave something behind?

230
00:17:58,369 --> 00:18:01,664
So I did a little research.

231
00:18:03,249 --> 00:18:07,587
What if you go to the welfare office
and apply for government assistance?

232
00:18:08,546 --> 00:18:09,881
It says here,

233
00:18:09,964 --> 00:18:14,427
you can use the welfare office
as your address if you don't have one.

234
00:18:14,511 --> 00:18:15,678
Have a look.

235
00:18:15,762 --> 00:18:19,766
I thought you're ineligible to receive aid
if you're fit to work.

236
00:18:19,849 --> 00:18:23,144
If you're struggling,
being healthy doesn't disqualify you.

237
00:18:23,228 --> 00:18:25,104
You pay your taxes.

238
00:18:26,523 --> 00:18:28,983
You'd have a better luck of landing a job

239
00:18:29,067 --> 00:18:32,320
if you apply for rent relief
and have a place of your own.

240
00:18:32,403 --> 00:18:34,531
Look, you were about to sleep
on the streets.

241
00:18:34,614 --> 00:18:36,366
You have every right to receive aid.

242
00:18:37,784 --> 00:18:40,703
I know a real estate agent.
They can help you find a rental.

243
00:18:41,371 --> 00:18:45,750
Here. A guide on how
to successfully apply for aid

244
00:18:45,834 --> 00:18:48,294
and a referral for the real estate agent.

245
00:18:53,633 --> 00:18:55,885
HOW TO SUCCESSFULLY
APPLY FOR AID - REFERRAL

246
00:19:02,892 --> 00:19:04,435
What is it?

247
00:19:05,937 --> 00:19:08,982
You're so generous,
I thought you were heaven-sent.

248
00:19:09,941 --> 00:19:11,943
You paid for consultation.

249
00:19:12,443 --> 00:19:14,904
Also, without a place to live,

250
00:19:14,988 --> 00:19:17,323
you might be tempted
to sleep on my property again.

251
00:19:17,824 --> 00:19:19,534
And that, I cannot have.

252
00:19:20,326 --> 00:19:21,578
I'll see you tomorrow.

253
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:29,586
Her tone though…

254
00:19:32,380 --> 00:19:34,048
Still, she's got a heart of gold.

255
00:19:36,426 --> 00:19:40,138
She might be unfriendly, but she's better
than a friendly person who betrays me.

256
00:19:58,156 --> 00:19:59,449
What is that?

257
00:20:00,366 --> 00:20:01,534
Fire?

258
00:20:30,980 --> 00:20:32,231
It's just a dream.

259
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:29,706
No way. That can't be right!

260
00:21:33,334 --> 00:21:34,836
Chloe!

261
00:21:37,463 --> 00:21:38,673
Chloe!

262
00:21:40,675 --> 00:21:41,926
Chloe!

263
00:21:44,095 --> 00:21:45,596
It's unlocked.

264
00:21:47,598 --> 00:21:48,891
Chloe?

265
00:21:52,395 --> 00:21:53,688
What a mansion!

266
00:21:55,648 --> 00:21:57,025
Chloe!

267
00:22:01,863 --> 00:22:02,989
Chloe?

268
00:22:05,575 --> 00:22:06,743
Hold on…

269
00:22:06,826 --> 00:22:07,994
Chloe!

270
00:22:13,291 --> 00:22:14,625
Chloe!

271
00:22:16,085 --> 00:22:17,295
Miss Emma?

272
00:22:17,378 --> 00:22:19,297
Glad you're okay. There's a fire.

273
00:22:20,840 --> 00:22:22,467
What's this stench? It smells.

274
00:22:22,550 --> 00:22:23,885
Do you have a fire extinguisher?

275
00:22:25,511 --> 00:22:27,096
I don't know.

276
00:22:27,180 --> 00:22:29,307
At any rate, we need to call
the fire department.

277
00:22:29,390 --> 00:22:30,641
That's…

278
00:22:31,976 --> 00:22:34,604
I have to change before they arrive.

279
00:22:36,355 --> 00:22:38,858
I'm gonna get changed.
Miss Emma, you call them.

280
00:22:38,941 --> 00:22:40,693
Hold on, I left my phone behind!

281
00:22:40,777 --> 00:22:43,112
In that case…

282
00:22:43,196 --> 00:22:45,990
There's the home phone
by the entrance. Use that.

283
00:22:48,659 --> 00:22:50,536
Goodness…

284
00:22:59,670 --> 00:23:01,005
There's a fire.

285
00:23:02,090 --> 00:23:03,216
A fire.

286
00:23:04,258 --> 00:23:05,426
My address?

287
00:23:05,510 --> 00:23:09,555
Chloe? Someone who lives here
should be calling…

288
00:23:10,056 --> 00:23:11,557
Give me a sec.

289
00:23:11,641 --> 00:23:13,684
Please stand by.

290
00:23:17,146 --> 00:23:22,235
We're in Mitaka, I think.
It's the fancy, big house in Mitaka.

291
00:23:23,236 --> 00:23:27,824
The fire was from a battery of a laptop
that hasn't been charged in ages.

292
00:23:28,366 --> 00:23:33,079
It then spread to the linseed oil in the
wall cabinet of the kitchen downstairs.

293
00:23:33,955 --> 00:23:36,707
Is this the fire predicted
by the fortune reading earlier?

294
00:23:37,416 --> 00:23:40,253
The main house was burned,
but not completely.

295
00:23:40,753 --> 00:23:43,422
She said she can stay
at the same guesthouse I was at

296
00:23:43,506 --> 00:23:45,842
while the main house underwent repairs,
so she can resume her life.

297
00:23:48,261 --> 00:23:51,597
And how did this incident
bring you fortune?

298
00:23:51,681 --> 00:23:55,810
She said I can stay
at the guesthouse with her.

299
00:23:55,893 --> 00:23:57,854
To repay me
for alerting her about the fire.

300
00:23:57,937 --> 00:23:59,355
What a miracle.

301
00:24:00,064 --> 00:24:04,235
But I still have to move out when
I save enough to rent my own place.

302
00:24:04,318 --> 00:24:07,697
At the latest, she wants me gone
by the time the repairs are complete.

303
00:24:08,197 --> 00:24:11,075
That's why I'm job hunting like this, but…

304
00:24:12,201 --> 00:24:15,079
All her predictions came true.

305
00:24:15,621 --> 00:24:17,456
What a shame it's just a hobby for her.

306
00:24:18,124 --> 00:24:20,084
That's what I thought too,

307
00:24:20,168 --> 00:24:22,587
so I suggested
she open a fortune-telling business.

308
00:24:22,670 --> 00:24:24,964
To my surprise, she wholeheartedly agreed.

309
00:24:25,047 --> 00:24:29,260
But she wants to do it hobby-level.
Keep it small.

310
00:24:29,343 --> 00:24:32,054
So she's only opening shop one day a week.

311
00:24:34,724 --> 00:24:37,810
I bet it'll become popular
in no time by word of mouth.

312
00:24:39,270 --> 00:24:42,690
I'm not sure.
She charges 3,000 yen per session.

313
00:24:43,816 --> 00:24:47,904
Also, Chloe isn't…
What do you call it? Friendly.

314
00:24:49,530 --> 00:24:52,450
I gathered that from your story.

315
00:24:52,533 --> 00:24:54,952
She really isn't.

316
00:24:55,036 --> 00:24:56,996
She makes biting remarks.

317
00:24:57,079 --> 00:24:59,165
She can learn to soften her tone.

318
00:24:59,665 --> 00:25:02,126
I know I shouldn't complain
considering her generosity,

319
00:25:02,210 --> 00:25:05,588
but it's like, our standard of living
couldn't be any more different.

320
00:25:05,671 --> 00:25:07,048
Standard of living?

321
00:25:07,131 --> 00:25:08,257
Yeah.

322
00:25:08,925 --> 00:25:12,887
I told her I'd like to do the chores
since I'm boarding rent-free,

323
00:25:12,970 --> 00:25:16,349
and then I made packaged ramen for lunch.

324
00:25:16,432 --> 00:25:18,351
But she was like,
"You can't call this cooking."

325
00:25:19,101 --> 00:25:21,938
Then, for dinner,
she said she wanted something with rice.

326
00:25:22,021 --> 00:25:25,441
But listen to this.
She doesn't even own a rice cooker.

327
00:25:26,150 --> 00:25:29,737
I see… Like, she prefers
to use a pressure cooker or a clay pot?

328
00:25:29,820 --> 00:25:31,364
Yes! Exactly.

329
00:25:31,447 --> 00:25:34,867
Rice sure is tasty
when it's cooked that way.

330
00:25:34,951 --> 00:25:38,037
But how do you keep it warm
without a rice cooker?

331
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:40,289
I mean, that's true, but…

332
00:25:41,374 --> 00:25:43,251
I worked a normal full-time job,

333
00:25:43,334 --> 00:25:45,336
so I never knew
people had these preferences.

334
00:25:46,170 --> 00:25:48,339
Though I've never used a clay pot
to cook rice,

335
00:25:48,422 --> 00:25:50,800
I gave it my best shot to make her happy.

336
00:25:54,303 --> 00:25:57,598
I can't stand it anymore.
This rice is burned and hard as rock.

337
00:25:58,641 --> 00:25:59,767
Sorry.

338
00:26:00,643 --> 00:26:04,897
You also made ramen
with half-cooked eggs mixed in the soup.

339
00:26:07,358 --> 00:26:12,446
If I overcook it, the noodles get soggy.
So the eggs have to be undercooked.

340
00:26:12,530 --> 00:26:14,699
Then make marinated eggs beforehand.

341
00:26:16,867 --> 00:26:20,246
I've seen those at the store.
I'll buy them next time.

342
00:26:20,329 --> 00:26:23,082
What? Just make them.

343
00:26:23,165 --> 00:26:24,875
Wouldn't it be faster to buy them?

344
00:26:28,045 --> 00:26:31,841
Miss Emma, you must be the type
to buy packaged shredded cabbage.

345
00:26:32,341 --> 00:26:33,509
Yes.

346
00:26:34,218 --> 00:26:38,014
I know it's more expensive that way,
but I can't eat the whole cabbage.

347
00:26:38,556 --> 00:26:42,101
It's more convenient to use pre-cut
vegetables, and I can finish it.

348
00:26:42,643 --> 00:26:46,272
You lived with your boyfriend, right?
Neither of you cooked?

349
00:26:46,355 --> 00:26:50,109
We both worked overtime.
We were wiped by the end of day.

350
00:26:50,192 --> 00:26:53,904
So we'd grab discounted sides
from the deli on the way home.

351
00:26:57,033 --> 00:26:58,451
It's like…

352
00:26:59,243 --> 00:27:00,328
What is it?

353
00:27:05,666 --> 00:27:06,751
Nothing.

354
00:27:08,627 --> 00:27:12,340
You've got your own approach to life.

355
00:27:15,760 --> 00:27:16,969
Have you heard?

356
00:27:17,053 --> 00:27:20,848
There's a new type of malnutrition
where you consume sufficient calories,

357
00:27:20,931 --> 00:27:23,351
but you're missing certain nutrients.

358
00:27:23,434 --> 00:27:27,813
Did you know? Chicken breast
and broccoli cover all bases.

359
00:27:29,231 --> 00:27:31,484
What are you, a bodybuilder?

360
00:27:32,068 --> 00:27:33,652
Of course not.

361
00:27:33,736 --> 00:27:35,738
I don't drink protein shakes.

362
00:27:37,615 --> 00:27:38,783
I thought so.

363
00:27:41,202 --> 00:27:44,872
We were brought up differently.

364
00:27:44,955 --> 00:27:46,832
No wonder our standard
of living is different.

365
00:27:57,760 --> 00:27:58,844
What is it?

366
00:28:01,806 --> 00:28:04,642
You've taken me under your wing.

367
00:28:05,267 --> 00:28:07,353
I'd like to be helpful to you.

368
00:28:10,189 --> 00:28:11,315
Well…

369
00:28:12,066 --> 00:28:15,277
If anything comes up,
I'll ask for your help.

370
00:28:16,695 --> 00:28:19,323
I'm gonna take a shower.

371
00:28:19,407 --> 00:28:21,826
I hate drying my hair.

372
00:28:24,662 --> 00:28:26,163
What? What is it?

373
00:28:27,206 --> 00:28:30,000
Your hair… I can dry it for you.

374
00:28:49,478 --> 00:28:50,646
How is it?

375
00:28:54,650 --> 00:28:56,485
This is quite nice.

376
00:28:56,569 --> 00:28:57,862
Really?

377
00:28:58,863 --> 00:29:01,407
I hate drying long hair.

378
00:29:01,490 --> 00:29:04,118
It takes forever and my arms get tired.

379
00:29:04,994 --> 00:29:07,163
Can I be in charge
of blow-drying your hair?

380
00:29:09,373 --> 00:29:10,749
I see.

381
00:29:10,833 --> 00:29:13,294
It's like shredded cabbage.

382
00:29:13,794 --> 00:29:17,506
You pay for the convenience
of not having to do it yourself.

383
00:29:18,507 --> 00:29:19,675
Now I see.

384
00:29:21,302 --> 00:29:22,803
Let me finish up.

385
00:29:31,854 --> 00:29:35,941
I end up helping out with meals anyway,

386
00:29:36,025 --> 00:29:37,568
as well as the laundry and cleaning.

387
00:29:39,320 --> 00:29:42,281
You know what, though?
Chloe sounds like a kind person.

388
00:29:43,949 --> 00:29:45,534
I suppose.

389
00:29:45,618 --> 00:29:47,620
I won't deny that.

390
00:29:47,703 --> 00:29:50,789
But she lacks friendliness
to the point I overlook her kindness,

391
00:29:50,873 --> 00:29:52,625
or she's flat-out rude.

392
00:29:53,334 --> 00:29:56,879
She openly said
your actions determine your future.

393
00:29:56,962 --> 00:30:01,050
She sounds like
an honest fortune teller to me.

394
00:30:03,594 --> 00:30:05,429
I'm still bothered somewhat.

395
00:30:19,985 --> 00:30:21,070
Say…

396
00:30:24,198 --> 00:30:27,451
Could I come in for a reading with her?

397
00:30:34,917 --> 00:30:36,252
That's the gist of it.

398
00:30:36,335 --> 00:30:38,337
I brought a guest for you.

399
00:30:39,922 --> 00:30:41,257
Nice to meet you.

400
00:30:44,134 --> 00:30:46,303
-Emma.
-Yes?

401
00:30:46,387 --> 00:30:49,390
I told you I see clients
only once a week, on Sundays.

402
00:30:50,849 --> 00:30:51,850
You're right.

403
00:30:52,434 --> 00:30:54,311
I'm so sorry. I totally forgot.

404
00:30:54,395 --> 00:30:58,607
It's fine. I came on a whim anyway.

405
00:31:00,901 --> 00:31:03,654
It's not like fortune-telling
can give me the answer I'm looking for.

406
00:31:11,161 --> 00:31:13,998
I'll go get ready.
Will you give me a second?

407
00:31:15,791 --> 00:31:18,961
Emma, please show her
to the divination room.

408
00:31:20,296 --> 00:31:21,338
Will do.

409
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:23,173
Thank you so much!

410
00:31:25,301 --> 00:31:26,385
Shall we?

411
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:33,058
Thank you for waiting.

412
00:31:33,976 --> 00:31:36,270
What a fit, Chloe.

413
00:31:36,353 --> 00:31:38,814
You look like
you stepped out of a magazine.

414
00:31:39,398 --> 00:31:41,692
Please step out
if you're not being seen today.

415
00:31:41,775 --> 00:31:43,235
We need privacy.

416
00:31:43,319 --> 00:31:44,695
Okay.

417
00:31:44,778 --> 00:31:46,113
Well, enjoy.

418
00:31:55,497 --> 00:31:59,960
Well then, please write down your name
and its pronunciation, your birthday,

419
00:32:00,586 --> 00:32:03,172
and your current address.

420
00:32:04,048 --> 00:32:05,132
Yes.

421
00:32:10,304 --> 00:32:11,847
YUKIKO KONAGAYA
MITAKA - DECEMBER 3RD, 1986

422
00:32:11,930 --> 00:32:14,183
Yukiko Konagaya.

423
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:19,313
What shall I read for you today?

424
00:32:23,233 --> 00:32:24,860
Well, I…

425
00:32:32,868 --> 00:32:35,663
I have a husband and a child.

426
00:32:36,872 --> 00:32:41,543
I married a high earner
and moved into a high-rise apartment.

427
00:32:42,169 --> 00:32:44,380
My child attends a private school.

428
00:32:45,839 --> 00:32:48,801
And yet, I can't escape
the wealth disparity

429
00:32:48,884 --> 00:32:50,719
that surrounds my daily life.

430
00:32:51,804 --> 00:32:53,639
-The wealth disparity?
-Yes.

431
00:32:54,723 --> 00:32:58,852
I obsess over the brand
of clothes and bags I own.

432
00:32:58,936 --> 00:33:00,187
On social media too.

433
00:33:00,729 --> 00:33:04,108
I play up my extravagant lifestyle
for everyone to see.

434
00:33:05,693 --> 00:33:07,611
I desperately try

435
00:33:08,737 --> 00:33:12,366
to keep up with the lifestyle
of those in my social circle.

436
00:33:16,829 --> 00:33:17,830
But then…

437
00:33:19,373 --> 00:33:22,584
Once, I was in the elevator with my child,

438
00:33:23,794 --> 00:33:27,506
and they judged
the people who live below us.

439
00:33:28,048 --> 00:33:31,343
Also, I was horrified
when my husband casually commented

440
00:33:31,427 --> 00:33:34,012
on the type of car
parked by the apartment entrance.

441
00:33:36,306 --> 00:33:38,142
At the same time,

442
00:33:38,225 --> 00:33:42,438
when my husband's parents chatter
boisterously at a high-end restaurant,

443
00:33:42,521 --> 00:33:44,398
I find myself judging them.

444
00:33:47,192 --> 00:33:50,195
I'm repulsed by my own family members,
who look down on others,

445
00:33:50,821 --> 00:33:55,325
but I'm no better than them.

446
00:34:02,750 --> 00:34:04,918
Being with my family tires me out.

447
00:34:07,337 --> 00:34:09,256
But I don't want to be alone.

448
00:34:15,429 --> 00:34:17,598
What am I supposed to do?

449
00:34:22,186 --> 00:34:24,772
As if you can tell me.

450
00:34:28,942 --> 00:34:30,569
Shall we ask the cards?

451
00:34:40,871 --> 00:34:42,456
Are they tarot cards?

452
00:34:43,916 --> 00:34:46,835
No. Chronicle cards.

453
00:34:46,919 --> 00:34:48,128
Chronicle cards?

454
00:34:49,546 --> 00:34:52,633
They're for reading
the flow of time, I suppose.

455
00:34:54,510 --> 00:34:57,596
There are twelve cards
from January to December,

456
00:34:57,679 --> 00:35:00,224
seven cards from Monday to Friday,

457
00:35:00,307 --> 00:35:03,393
and one additional card,

458
00:35:03,477 --> 00:35:04,812
totaling 20 cards.

459
00:35:05,646 --> 00:35:07,356
Each card represents a different concept,

460
00:35:08,315 --> 00:35:11,401
and their meaning changes
depending on their position.

461
00:35:12,194 --> 00:35:13,320
Fascinating…

462
00:35:14,738 --> 00:35:18,408
I will now read your fortune
by randomly selecting five cards.

463
00:35:33,006 --> 00:35:34,591
Oh,

464
00:35:34,675 --> 00:35:36,093
mon…

465
00:35:36,176 --> 00:35:37,261
Dieu!

466
00:36:29,938 --> 00:36:31,857
The first card.

467
00:36:32,733 --> 00:36:34,693
It represents your current situation.

468
00:36:36,361 --> 00:36:39,448
February, upright. Card of Solitude.

469
00:36:41,325 --> 00:36:43,243
Though you adorn yourself, you are lonely.

470
00:36:43,744 --> 00:36:46,496
Your relationships are platonic.

471
00:36:48,040 --> 00:36:52,044
In your mind, you love your family.

472
00:36:57,758 --> 00:36:58,842
The second card.

473
00:36:59,718 --> 00:37:03,013
It represents something from
the past that continues to affect you.

474
00:37:06,642 --> 00:37:08,477
May, upright.

475
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:10,228
Card of Tradition.

476
00:37:11,855 --> 00:37:14,191
It represents traditional values,

477
00:37:14,274 --> 00:37:15,859
or an enclosed space.

478
00:37:17,152 --> 00:37:18,153
It could also…

479
00:37:18,737 --> 00:37:21,198
signify a patriarchal system.

480
00:37:24,868 --> 00:37:28,121
The third card. The inner self.

481
00:37:30,707 --> 00:37:33,710
Monday, upright. Card of Hesitation.

482
00:37:35,921 --> 00:37:36,964
There's a hesitation.

483
00:37:37,881 --> 00:37:40,175
It's the kind that comes with a secret.

484
00:37:41,843 --> 00:37:43,470
For example, a love triangle,

485
00:37:44,429 --> 00:37:45,597
or marriage…

486
00:37:47,015 --> 00:37:48,433
Could it be romantic?

487
00:37:50,143 --> 00:37:53,855
It's upright,
meaning the situation isn't messy.

488
00:38:00,070 --> 00:38:01,071
Well…

489
00:38:02,030 --> 00:38:04,825
if you don't want to talk about it,
I won't pry.

490
00:38:05,367 --> 00:38:07,327
But does it ring a bell?

491
00:38:09,997 --> 00:38:11,039
Yes it does.

492
00:38:16,294 --> 00:38:19,381
The fourth card. The outer world.

493
00:38:22,134 --> 00:38:25,387
Thursday, reversed. Card of Greed.

494
00:38:27,597 --> 00:38:28,890
It seems you've grown weary

495
00:38:29,474 --> 00:38:32,102
of lavishness and intimate relationships.

496
00:38:38,483 --> 00:38:39,651
The final card.

497
00:38:40,777 --> 00:38:43,447
It represents an event in the near future.

498
00:38:45,824 --> 00:38:48,994
January, upright. Card of Encounter.

499
00:38:50,704 --> 00:38:54,041
A good encounter awaits you.

500
00:38:54,958 --> 00:38:56,251
A meeting with new beginnings.

501
00:38:58,253 --> 00:38:59,796
And…

502
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:01,673
I see a park,

503
00:39:01,757 --> 00:39:03,008
or a game.

504
00:39:08,055 --> 00:39:09,681
Your lucky color is yellow.

505
00:39:11,641 --> 00:39:12,809
My lucky color?

506
00:39:14,561 --> 00:39:15,771
It's nothing.

507
00:39:17,773 --> 00:39:19,274
A good encounter, then?

508
00:39:21,234 --> 00:39:22,319
That's correct.

509
00:39:41,421 --> 00:39:43,799
What was the reading about?

510
00:39:45,342 --> 00:39:46,384
What was it about?

511
00:39:47,052 --> 00:39:49,054
She wanted to know about her family.

512
00:39:50,472 --> 00:39:51,473
Her family?

513
00:39:52,349 --> 00:39:54,101
Does she have a family?

514
00:39:54,810 --> 00:39:56,061
Why do you ask?

515
00:39:56,812 --> 00:39:59,648
Oh, I was just wondering.

516
00:39:59,731 --> 00:40:03,819
I ran into her at the unemployment center,
but I don't know anything else.

517
00:40:03,902 --> 00:40:06,071
Say what? The unemployment center?

518
00:40:06,154 --> 00:40:07,239
Yes.

519
00:40:08,782 --> 00:40:11,201
You met an affluent married woman
at the unemployment center?

520
00:40:12,369 --> 00:40:13,370
Affluent?

521
00:40:14,037 --> 00:40:17,874
Also, I can't shake this feeling
that I've seen her before.

522
00:40:20,377 --> 00:40:21,545
Now I'm curious.

523
00:40:31,471 --> 00:40:33,181
This is it. Found it.

524
00:40:34,558 --> 00:40:36,351
Huh? Found what?

525
00:40:36,434 --> 00:40:39,437
She's a lifestyle influencer.

526
00:40:39,521 --> 00:40:42,107
Yukiko Kamii, AKA "Camille."

527
00:40:42,190 --> 00:40:44,609
I must've recognized her
from an online interview or something.

528
00:40:44,693 --> 00:40:46,111
Take a look at this.

529
00:40:47,362 --> 00:40:50,240
Camille herself had stopped
uploading new content six months ago.

530
00:40:50,323 --> 00:40:51,324
CAMILLEKIKO

531
00:40:51,408 --> 00:40:54,661
But I found a mutual mom friend,

532
00:40:54,744 --> 00:40:57,372
then I dug into her network.

533
00:40:57,455 --> 00:40:59,082
Chloe?

534
00:40:59,166 --> 00:41:00,876
Apparently, her husband
declared bankruptcy,

535
00:41:00,959 --> 00:41:03,170
and she's separated from her family.

536
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:05,922
"Konagaya" must be her former surname.

537
00:41:06,006 --> 00:41:09,551
You found all that within hours.
You're a detective!

538
00:41:12,053 --> 00:41:15,056
But why did she want to know
her past self's fortune?

539
00:41:16,516 --> 00:41:19,019
She paid 3,000 yen for that?

540
00:41:20,228 --> 00:41:23,440
Usually, people refrain from lying
during a reading.

541
00:41:23,523 --> 00:41:26,359
You see, lying can alter the outcome.

542
00:41:27,777 --> 00:41:29,279
I see.

543
00:41:29,362 --> 00:41:32,073
While she must've had genuine concerns,

544
00:41:32,908 --> 00:41:37,412
if her family's torn apart,
then her issues should be resolved.

545
00:41:42,209 --> 00:41:44,628
Maybe she wanted to know

546
00:41:44,711 --> 00:41:47,505
what she could've done differently
to change her fate.

547
00:41:51,760 --> 00:41:53,637
Who knows what goes on in people's heads?

548
00:41:55,513 --> 00:41:59,392
Fortune-telling can only reveal
your present

549
00:41:59,476 --> 00:42:02,062
and provide a path forward.

550
00:42:05,440 --> 00:42:07,442
Shall I pour something warm to drink?

551
00:42:09,236 --> 00:42:10,320
Thank you.

552
00:42:17,410 --> 00:42:22,374
CAMILLEKIKO

553
00:42:23,458 --> 00:42:26,628
Off we go to a fusion Japanese restaurant!

554
00:42:30,006 --> 00:42:31,883
We might've walked too far.

555
00:42:32,509 --> 00:42:34,803
Have we? Then let's turn around.

556
00:42:34,886 --> 00:42:36,680
Sorry…

557
00:42:36,763 --> 00:42:38,974
No, I put you in charge of the directions.

558
00:42:39,057 --> 00:42:43,895
It's nothing compared to
your generous offer to pay for lunch.

559
00:42:43,979 --> 00:42:45,855
I can't wait
to try the fusion Japanese food.

560
00:42:46,690 --> 00:42:50,151
Will you memorize the flavor
and recreate the recipe?

561
00:42:50,235 --> 00:42:52,529
What? I can't do that.

562
00:42:56,866 --> 00:42:57,951
Would you like one?

563
00:42:58,785 --> 00:43:00,036
Oh, what?

564
00:43:01,621 --> 00:43:03,373
Would you like one?

565
00:43:04,416 --> 00:43:05,625
Would you like one?

566
00:43:08,586 --> 00:43:09,796
Would you like one?

567
00:43:12,882 --> 00:43:13,967
Would you like one?

568
00:43:18,346 --> 00:43:19,514
It is you.

569
00:43:21,850 --> 00:43:25,353
There's something I want to ask, Konagaya.

570
00:43:26,438 --> 00:43:29,316
Sorry. As you can see, I'm on the clock.

571
00:43:31,318 --> 00:43:32,986
-Emma.
-Yes.

572
00:43:33,069 --> 00:43:35,655
Help her pass out the tissues.

573
00:43:35,739 --> 00:43:36,740
Say what?

574
00:43:36,823 --> 00:43:39,034
I'm counting on you.
I'll see you at Paris.

575
00:43:39,576 --> 00:43:40,869
Bring her when you're done.

576
00:43:43,288 --> 00:43:45,206
What about the fusion Japanese cuisine?

577
00:43:45,290 --> 00:43:46,458
Paris?

578
00:43:48,418 --> 00:43:51,713
Sorry to bother you so suddenly.

579
00:43:51,796 --> 00:43:54,174
Paris is the name of a traditional café.

580
00:43:54,966 --> 00:43:58,303
What business
does that fortune teller have with me?

581
00:43:59,179 --> 00:44:03,016
She wants to get to the bottom
of a mystery.

582
00:44:03,099 --> 00:44:04,184
A mystery?

583
00:44:05,352 --> 00:44:07,437
Something about a person named Camille.

584
00:44:16,237 --> 00:44:20,158
TRADITIONAL CAFÉ PARIS

585
00:44:24,621 --> 00:44:25,789
Welcome in.

586
00:44:28,875 --> 00:44:30,251
Sorry to impose.

587
00:44:30,335 --> 00:44:33,046
-It's quite all right.
-Have you eaten yet?

588
00:44:33,963 --> 00:44:36,383
This café's famous for a dish.
Would you like to try it?

589
00:44:37,342 --> 00:44:38,551
My treat.

590
00:44:39,594 --> 00:44:40,637
What?

591
00:44:45,433 --> 00:44:46,434
Enjoy.

592
00:44:48,269 --> 00:44:50,730
Egg sandwich. It's very delicious.

593
00:44:51,481 --> 00:44:53,066
Thank you very much.

594
00:44:53,817 --> 00:44:55,568
One for you too, Emma.

595
00:44:57,070 --> 00:44:58,696
-Can I have one?
-Of course.

596
00:44:58,780 --> 00:45:00,573
Thank you so much.

597
00:45:02,283 --> 00:45:05,578
This is Simon.
When I collapsed by Chloe's front porch,

598
00:45:05,662 --> 00:45:08,415
he gave me whole wheat cookies.

599
00:45:08,498 --> 00:45:09,499
Come again?

600
00:45:09,582 --> 00:45:11,584
The cookies that can power you
through the day.

601
00:45:11,668 --> 00:45:13,878
What exactly are you talking about, Emma?

602
00:45:13,962 --> 00:45:17,298
Simon runs this café,
despite being so young.

603
00:45:18,049 --> 00:45:19,426
It was passed down to me though.

604
00:45:20,510 --> 00:45:21,511
Please, enjoy.

605
00:45:24,389 --> 00:45:26,266
-Thank you for the food.
-Thank you.

606
00:45:38,862 --> 00:45:39,946
It's fantastic.

607
00:45:50,540 --> 00:45:53,585
Why did you want to know the fortune
of your past self?

608
00:45:56,045 --> 00:46:00,842
When Chloe slipped into
that gorgeous dress, it hit me.

609
00:46:02,635 --> 00:46:04,888
Were you reminded
of when you were Camille?

610
00:46:05,430 --> 00:46:06,723
Indeed.

611
00:46:06,806 --> 00:46:09,809
I used to live that way too.

612
00:46:10,435 --> 00:46:14,856
Then, I felt ashamed of who I'd become.

613
00:46:15,523 --> 00:46:18,860
That's why I pretended to be my old self.

614
00:46:22,697 --> 00:46:25,992
I've separated from my husband,
and I no longer live with my child.

615
00:46:26,075 --> 00:46:27,368
I live alone in an apartment.

616
00:46:28,578 --> 00:46:31,080
I thought I was finally set free,

617
00:46:31,164 --> 00:46:33,249
that I don't have to perform anymore.

618
00:46:34,834 --> 00:46:37,462
You should've asked
for the fortune of your current self.

619
00:46:37,545 --> 00:46:39,464
Why throw away 3,000 yen like that?

620
00:46:40,715 --> 00:46:43,927
My question would have been
the same regardless.

621
00:46:44,552 --> 00:46:45,553
What?

622
00:46:48,056 --> 00:46:50,517
What am I supposed to do?

623
00:46:51,601 --> 00:46:53,811
I keep asking myself
the same old question.

624
00:47:01,945 --> 00:47:05,615
Emma, that's the very question you had
when I read your fortune.

625
00:47:05,698 --> 00:47:06,741
Huh?

626
00:47:07,408 --> 00:47:08,701
Did I?

627
00:47:09,661 --> 00:47:12,539
Maybe that's everyone's question
when they want to know their fortune.

628
00:47:13,581 --> 00:47:16,125
"What am I supposed to do?"

629
00:47:17,210 --> 00:47:18,628
It's a common thread among
us unemployed folks.

630
00:47:21,464 --> 00:47:23,174
Sorry to intrude.

631
00:47:23,258 --> 00:47:25,134
Chocolate banana crunch parfait.

632
00:47:27,428 --> 00:47:29,472
That looks delectable!

633
00:47:29,556 --> 00:47:30,557
Here.

634
00:47:31,224 --> 00:47:32,725
If you'd like.

635
00:47:32,809 --> 00:47:36,187
It's off the menu.
I had Simon make it just for us.

636
00:47:38,064 --> 00:47:41,025
It uses homemade nougat chocolate crunch.

637
00:47:41,109 --> 00:47:45,238
The pieces of pie crust and cookies
give it a nice crunch.

638
00:47:45,321 --> 00:47:46,990
-Homemade?
-Yes.

639
00:47:47,073 --> 00:47:49,450
Simon's hobby is parfait-making.

640
00:47:49,534 --> 00:47:51,077
Hobby, huh?

641
00:47:51,953 --> 00:47:54,038
-Hence it's off the menu.
-Yes.

642
00:47:54,622 --> 00:47:58,585
Simon visits Chloe's place
every week to make parfaits.

643
00:47:58,668 --> 00:48:02,005
That's why he was there
when she read my fortune.

644
00:48:02,672 --> 00:48:06,342
The whole wheat cookies you had
were leftovers from a parfait.

645
00:48:07,635 --> 00:48:09,012
That's something else.

646
00:48:09,095 --> 00:48:13,600
I've heard of sushi masters visiting
the wealthy to make sushi, but…

647
00:48:15,143 --> 00:48:17,020
-Thank you.
-Bon appétit.

648
00:48:17,103 --> 00:48:18,354
Time to dig in.

649
00:48:28,573 --> 00:48:29,657
This is delicious.

650
00:48:30,700 --> 00:48:32,076
Hey, Konayuki!

651
00:48:33,536 --> 00:48:34,662
Konayuki?

652
00:48:35,788 --> 00:48:39,417
I'm Yukiko Konagaya. Konayuki for short.

653
00:48:39,500 --> 00:48:41,794
It came up
while we were passing out tissues.

654
00:48:41,878 --> 00:48:45,006
This could be my lucky color. Brown!

655
00:48:46,174 --> 00:48:48,593
Yellow… that's my lucky color.

656
00:48:48,676 --> 00:48:50,470
Whoa, this parfait has both!

657
00:48:51,387 --> 00:48:53,222
It's an auspicious
chocolate banana parfait!

658
00:49:07,945 --> 00:49:12,617
Konayuki, how are you doing,
compared to before?

659
00:49:14,369 --> 00:49:17,372
Actually, I found a job.

660
00:49:17,914 --> 00:49:19,957
I'm working part-time until it starts.

661
00:49:20,041 --> 00:49:21,042
Really?

662
00:49:21,709 --> 00:49:23,711
She beat you to it, Emma.

663
00:49:24,962 --> 00:49:27,340
I want to earn a proper wage

664
00:49:27,423 --> 00:49:29,801
so that I can gain custody
of my child someday.

665
00:49:30,510 --> 00:49:33,179
Currently, my in-laws are watching them.

666
00:49:34,097 --> 00:49:35,139
I see.

667
00:49:36,849 --> 00:49:40,186
I want to play with my child at a park
where there are no moms

668
00:49:40,269 --> 00:49:42,313
trying to outcompete one another.

669
00:49:43,064 --> 00:49:47,318
I want my child to grow up to be
a kind person who doesn't judge others.

670
00:49:54,409 --> 00:49:56,411
"Influencer,"

671
00:49:56,494 --> 00:49:58,621
"wife," "mother"…

672
00:49:59,580 --> 00:50:03,668
It feels like a burden has been lifted
now that I'm none of these things.

673
00:50:05,336 --> 00:50:10,216
But… it's a bit lonely
to come home to an empty apartment.

674
00:50:14,679 --> 00:50:16,472
But this is who I am right now.

675
00:50:17,724 --> 00:50:20,852
This is me, without a filter.

676
00:50:28,484 --> 00:50:29,819
Then…

677
00:50:32,572 --> 00:50:33,698
How about,

678
00:50:34,699 --> 00:50:38,286
you come to this café
whenever you feel lonely?

679
00:50:39,287 --> 00:50:40,496
What?

680
00:50:41,247 --> 00:50:43,958
This off-menu parfait costs 480 yen.

681
00:50:44,041 --> 00:50:45,668
Why not stop by sometime?

682
00:50:46,586 --> 00:50:49,672
Otherwise,
it's mostly elderly regulars here.

683
00:50:51,466 --> 00:50:52,967
Thank you very much.

684
00:50:53,634 --> 00:50:58,347
But it's hard to come
to a café full of regulars.

685
00:50:59,849 --> 00:51:01,100
The elderly customers

686
00:51:01,184 --> 00:51:03,728
primarily visit before noon and afternoon.

687
00:51:03,811 --> 00:51:06,814
This place is empty
during lunchtime and evenings.

688
00:51:08,983 --> 00:51:13,613
I get it. Café regulars
can be a bit too friendly.

689
00:51:14,155 --> 00:51:17,658
Sometimes, you want to be
by yourself but not alone.

690
00:51:18,201 --> 00:51:21,829
Like, you're not completely forgotten,
but you're also not talking to anyone.

691
00:51:24,665 --> 00:51:27,585
Emma, what if you work here

692
00:51:27,668 --> 00:51:30,296
and discourage the other customers
from approaching her?

693
00:51:31,297 --> 00:51:36,135
You're getting ahead of yourself.
This isn't your café.

694
00:51:36,219 --> 00:51:38,513
Actually, she owns this café.

695
00:51:39,055 --> 00:51:39,889
Come again?

696
00:51:39,972 --> 00:51:42,683
She hired me to run the place.

697
00:51:43,351 --> 00:51:45,353
What? Really?

698
00:51:45,937 --> 00:51:48,606
What if you work here on weekdays

699
00:51:48,689 --> 00:51:51,692
and be my assistant
for my fortune-telling on weekends?

700
00:51:51,776 --> 00:51:55,321
Then you can save up,
find a place, and move out.

701
00:51:55,947 --> 00:52:00,117
Of course, you may wait
for your government aid to be approved.

702
00:52:00,201 --> 00:52:02,453
No. I'd love to work here.

703
00:52:02,537 --> 00:52:04,247
Thank you so much!

704
00:52:04,330 --> 00:52:05,623
It worked out for you.

705
00:52:05,706 --> 00:52:09,335
Oh, Konayuki.
This is all thanks to my lucky color.

706
00:52:09,418 --> 00:52:12,088
The fried piroshki from the other day,
this parfait…

707
00:52:12,588 --> 00:52:14,048
Lucky color…

708
00:52:14,715 --> 00:52:16,259
A good encounter, huh.

709
00:52:19,679 --> 00:52:21,389
Let's both do our best.

710
00:52:22,181 --> 00:52:23,182
Yes.

711
00:52:24,183 --> 00:52:26,978
I might stop by if you're working here.

712
00:52:27,562 --> 00:52:28,771
By all means!

713
00:52:29,814 --> 00:52:33,526
Your action determines
your future, correct?

714
00:52:35,945 --> 00:52:37,238
Emma,

715
00:52:37,321 --> 00:52:41,033
I hope you learn
the egg sandwich recipe, at least.

716
00:52:41,701 --> 00:52:43,327
Yes. I'll give it my all.

717
00:52:53,921 --> 00:52:55,047
Yum!

718
00:55:02,091 --> 00:55:04,677
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION
